UMLAZI - The case of seven men accused of several murders at the notorious Glebelands hostel in Umlazi is being heard on Tuesday. The men are applying for bail in the Durban Regional Court. A police officer has been implicated in the killings. READ: Glebelands 'hitman' sent to prison for life According to the charge sheet, the accused “and certain other persons conspired to form a syndicate with the common purpose to kill persons residing at Glebelands in order to take control of the aforesaid hostel and thereby acquire control of payments made by dwellers at the hostel”. The hostel has been the centre of political violence for decades, with over 90 people killed. - Additional reporting by ANA eNCA